# AnalogGauges
Weekend project to turn some analog gauges I picked up at a surplus store into something useful.

![Gauge Assembly](/Images/FullAssembly.jpg?raw=true "Gauge Assembly")

These gauges serve as a desk ornament indicating current internet download speed and latency.  A [Particle Photon](https://store.particle.io/products/photon) to drives the gauges and is coupled with [HomeAssistant](https://home-assistant.io/) to run periodic speedtests.


Repository Contents
-------------------

* **/Hardware**
    - STL files for gauges and gauge enclosure.
    - Gauge Legends
* **/Software**
    - Example HomeAssistant configuration.yaml
    - Portable library for driving the gauges as well as complete sketch for this (speedtes display) application.
* **/Images** - Images of the completed gauge assembly.


